        <abstract> 
<p>Is JDH sure it is a <hi rend="italic">Bletia</hi>, just received? Its pollen very different from any Epidendreæ he has seen. If it is <hi rend="italic">Bletia</hi>, Lindley’s grand divisions are fanciful.</p> 
            <p>Accepts JDH’s offer to collect cases of dimorphism.</p> 
<p>James Bateman has sent a lot of orchids with <hi rend="italic">Angraecum sesquipedale</hi>. What a proboscis the moth that sucks its 11½ inch nectary must have!</p> 
